Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: basicconfigparser
Version: 0.1
Summary: A basic configuration file parser module for Python. 
Home-page: https://github.com/phr4nz/basicconfigparser
Author: Francesco Palumbo
Author-email: franzopal@gmail.com
License: GPL3
Description: A basic configuration file parser module for Python. It is a simple function which takes a file path a dictionary of rules (regex based) an optional key value separator (default is '='), an optional character to identify lines which start with a comment (default '#'), and returns a dictionary containing parsed data. No sections or others things are required. The eventually rised exceptions contain error line number.
Platform: UNKNOWN
Classifier: Intended Audience :: Developers
Classifier: License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 or later (GPLv3+)
Classifier: Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux
Classifier: Programming Language :: Python
